2. Stoichiometry
Stoichiometry (Greek: stoicheion = element, metron = measure) is the quantitative relationship between
reactants and products in a chemical reaction. It is the backbone of pollution load calculations, water treatment
dosing, and atmospheric chemistry modelling.
2.1 The Mole Concept
