Process DG Relevance
Biodegradation of pollutants Microbes exploit reactions with negative DG for energy
Heavy metal speciation DG determines which ionic form is stable in soil/water
Acid mine drainage Pyrite oxidation is highly spontaneous (large -DG)
Photosynthesis +DG reaction driven by solar energy (non-spontaneous)
Ozone depletion CFC + On ® products has -DG (thermodynamically favoured)
