8.3 Alkalinity and Buffering
Total Alkalinity = HCOnn + 2COn²n + OHn - Hn (in equivalents). Alkalinity resists pH changes (buffers).
Natural waters with high alkalinity (high HCOnn) are more resistant to acid rain. Alkalinity is expressed in mg/L
as CaCOn.
8.4 Ocean Acidification
Ocean Acidification Mechanism
Rising atmospheric COn ® more COn dissolves in ocean ® more HnCOn forms ® more Hn released ®
pH drops. Ocean pH has fallen from 8.2 to 8.1 since industrialisation (a 26% increase in Hn concentration).
Impact: COn²n concentration decreases ® coral reefs and shell-forming organisms (pteropods, molluscs)
cannot form CaCOn shells ® bleaching and dissolution.
