Q6. Benzo[a]pyrene is classified as which type of compound?
(a) Aliphatic hydrocarbon
(b) Polycyclic Aromatic Hydrocarbon (PAH)
(c) Alkene
(d) Chlorofluorocarbon
4 Answer: (b)
Explanation: Benzo[a]pyrene has 5 fused benzene rings. It is a PAH produced by incomplete combustion (tobacco,
grilled food, diesel exhaust) and is classified as IARC Group 1 carcinogen.
Q7. The half-life of Cs-137 is approximately 30 years. After 90 years, what fraction of the original Cs-137
remains?
(a) 1/2
(b) 1/4
(c) 1/8
(d) 1/16
4 Answer: (c)
Explanation: 90 years = 3 half-lives. After 1 t½: 1/2; after 2 t½: 1/4; after 3 t½: 1/8. Use N = Nn × (1/2)^(t/t½) = Nn ×
(1/2)³ = Nn/8.
Q8. Which of the following increases when temperature increases?
(a) Dissolved oxygen in water
(b) Solubility of On
(c) Biological Oxygen Demand rate
(d) Henry's constant for On (decreasing solubility)
4 Answer: (c)
Explanation: Higher temperature ® faster microbial metabolism ® faster BOD rate. DO and On solubility
DECREASE with temperature (Henry's Kn increases). Option (d) is true but is stated as a result not an increase in
solubility.
